1. What is Hover Action?
- Hover (Mouse over) means moving the mouse pointer over an element without clicking it.
- In web applications, hovering is used to:
    - Show dropdown menus
    - Display tooltips
    - Reveal hidden buttons(Edit/Delete)
    - Trigger Animations

2. Selenium Tool Used
- We use
    from selenium.webdriver.common.action_chains import ActionChains

- class used -> ActionChains(driver)

3. Basic Syntax
- Syntax
    actions = ActionChains(driver)
    actions.move_to_element(element).perform

4. Simple Example (Hover Demo)

from selenium import webdriver
from selenium.webdriver.common.by import By
from selenium.webdriver.common.action_chains import ActionChains
import time

driver = webdriver.Chrome()
driver.get("https://the-internet.herokuapp.com/hovers")
driver.maximize_window()


element = driver.find_element(By.XPATH, "(//div[@class='figure'])[1]")

actions = ActionChains(driver)
actions.move_to_element(element).perform()

# click hidden link after hover
time.sleep(2)
driver.find_element(By.XPATH, "(//a[text()='View profile'])[1]").click()


print("Hover action completed")
driver.quit()

5. Types of Hover Actions
- Simple Hover
    actions.move_to_perform(element).perform()

- Hover + Click
    actions.move_to_element(element).click().perform()

- Hover on Menu (real-time)
    actions.move_to_element(menu).perform()
    driver.find_element(By.LINK_TEXT, "Sub Menu").click()

6. Real Time Use Cases
- Amazon menu hover(Departments)
- Flipkart category hover
- Dropdown navigation menus
- Tooltip validation
- Hidden buttons(Edit/Delete icons)

7. Common Issues & Fixes
❌ Hover not working ✔ Fix: add wait / ActionChains re-initialize
❌ Element not visible ✔ Fix: scroll into view
    driver.execute_script("arguments[0].scrollIntoView();", element)

❌ Dynamic menu disappears ✔ Fix: use explicit wait

8. Best Practices
- Always use explicit wais
- Avoid time.sleep in real frameworks
- Re-initialize ActionChains if needed
- Use stable locators

